# Accessibility PR Checklist

- [ ] Component/story has keyboard support (tab order, enter/space to activate)
- [ ] Focus states are visible and meet contrast requirements
- [ ] All interactive elements include accessible names (labels, aria-label, or aria-labelledby)
- [ ] Images that convey meaning have alt text or proper role
- [ ] Color contrast meets WCAG AA for normal text (4.5:1) and large text (3:1)
- [ ] Dynamic content has announcements or live region handling
- [ ] Storybook story added/updated for the component
- [ ] Unit / integration tests added where appropriate
- [ ] Pa11y / axe / Lighthouse checks run and results attached
- [ ] Manual screen‑reader check recorded (who, what environment, summary)

If any item is not applicable, explain why in the PR description.
